# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat: new feature
# * fix: bug fix
# * docs: documentation
# * style: formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change
# * refactor: refactoring production code
# * test: adding tests, refactoring test; no production code change
# * chore: updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change

# Scope is optional and should be the feature/module being changed

# Subject should be imperative, lower case and not end with a period
# No more than 50 characters

# Body should explain what and why you have done something
# Wrap it to about 72 characters or so

# Footer should contain any BREAKING CHANGE and issue references